==== Functionality ====

The MetaDataSourceProvider allows to apply an existing provider to a parameterized data source.
This is achieved by referencing an existing RDFProvider, XMLProvider, or R2RMLProvider.
These providers can reference a data source, which contains a parameter {par}, typically in
the data source location URL.

The MetaDataSourceProvider specifies a query which can project an arbitrary number of parameter values.
Any column is treated as a parameter and the provider is run for each result row with the parameter replacement
shown in the example below.

This approach is suitable for cases, where the number of data sources is very dynamic and it is not
feasible to define one data source for each instance.

==== Example ====

Datasource with a parameterized location URL:

<source>
location = 'http://example.org/REST/{par}'
</source>

MetaDataSourceProvider Query:

<source>
query = 'select ?par where ?source ex:hasParameter ?par'
</source>
